"title": "8642: celebration",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8642: celebration",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Although there are examples of private celebrations in Scripture, most celebration is associated with the acts of God. The enemies of God's people also celebrate, but in the end it is the triumph of God's purpose that is celebrated.</p>\n<h2>Celebrations in everyday life</h2>\n<p>Wedding:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg14:10\">JDG 14:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:2-Matt22:3\">MAT 22:2–22:3</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:6\">MAT 14:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:21-Mark6:22\">MRK 6:21–6:22</a> <em>birthday</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:29\">LUK 5:29</a> <em>for an honoured guest</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:22-Luke15:24\">LUK 15:22–15:24</a> <em>family reunion</em></p>\n<h2>The Israelites celebrated God's acts</h2>\n<h3>Celebrating God's gifts of harvest: Pentecost and Tabernacles</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:16\">EXO 23:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:22\">EXO 34:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:15-Lev23:21\">LEV 23:15–23:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:33-Lev23:36\">LEV 23:33–23:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:39-Lev23:43\">LEV 23:39–23:43</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:26\">NUM 28:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:12\">NUM 29:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:9-Deut16:10\">DEU 16:9–16:10</a></p>\n<h3>Celebrating their deliverance from slavery in Egypt: Passover</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:3\">EXO 13:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:14\">EXO 12:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:15\">EXO 23:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:18\">EXO 34:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:2\">NUM 9:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:1\">DEU 16:1</a></p>\n<h3>Celebrating the deliverance of the nation through Esther: Purim</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth9:18-Esth9:19\">EST 9:18–9:19</a></p>\n<h2>Religious celebrations</h2>\n<h3>The bringing of the ark of the covenant to Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:12-2Sam6:15\">2SA 6:12–6:15</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:27-1Chr15:28\">1CH 15:27–15:28</a></p>\n<h3>The bringing of the ark of the covenant to the temple</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:3-1Kgs8:6\">1KI 8:3–8:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:4-2Chr5:6\">2CH 5:4–5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:12-2Chr5:13\">2CH 5:12–5:13</a></p>\n<h3>The completion and dedication of the first temple</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:63\">1KI 8:63</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:65-1Kgs8:66\">1KI 8:65–8:66</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:8-2Chr7:10\">2CH 7:8–7:10</a></p>\n<h3>The dedication of the second temple</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:16\">EZR 6:16</a></p>\n<h3>The reading of the law after the building of the walls of Jersualem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:9-Neh8:12\">NEH 8:9–8:12</a></p>\n<h3>Christians celebrate the death of Christ and his return</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:26\">1CO 11:26</a></p>\n<h2>The enemies of God's people celebrate</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:23\">JDG 16:23</a> <em>capture of Samson</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:1\">DAN 5:1</a> <em>Belshazzar's feast</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:3\">REV 11:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:7-Rev11:10\">REV 11:7–11:10</a></p>\n<h2>Celebration in heaven</h2>\n<h3>Creation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:4-Job38:7\">JOB 38:4–38:7</a></p>\n<h3>The repentance of sinners</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:7\">LUK 15:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:10\">LUK 15:10</a></p>\n<h3>Divine deliverance through Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:9-Rev5:10\">REV 5:9–5:10</a></p>\n<h3>The downfall of evil</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:1-Rev19:5\">REV 19:1–19:5</a></p>\n<h3>The final triumph of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:9\">REV 19:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:16-Rev11:18\">REV 11:16–11:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:2-Rev15:4\">REV 15:2–15:4</a></p>",
